style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#nasadiya-sukta-from-rigveda" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>In English we can call it Hymn of Creation. This is part of 10th mandala of the Rigveda (10:129). It is contemplating on the cosmology and the origin of the universe. This is one of the oldest text from Bhartiya Rishis. It has only 7 slokas and it goes like following.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Samskrut Video Links</title><link>https://dasarpai.github.io/samskrutyatra/samskrut-video-links/</link><pubDate>Mon, 22 Jul 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author><guid>https://dasarpai.github.io/samskrutyatra/samskrut-video-links/</guid><description>&lt;p>
